SUMMARY:CCC Requiem
DESCRIPTION:Organized by: ["Chester Children's Chorus"]\\nCategory: Perform
 ance\\nJoin the Chester Children’s Chorus for a moving performance of Mo
 zart’s Requiem on Sunday\, March 8\, 2026. One of the most profound wor
 ks in the choral repertoire\, Mozart's Requiem will be performed alongside
  30 community singers\, professional soloists\, and an orchestra\, bringin
 g together generations of voices and musicians. This masterpiece\, perfor
 med only every three to four years\, holds special meaning for the Chorus 
 and reflects the children's focus\, discipline\, and joy.  Admission is 
 free and open to the public. Seating is limited and available on a first-
 come\, first-served basis.  Guests are invited to a reception following 
 the concert in the lobby of the Lang Music Building. The event will also 
 be livestreamed on the CCC's Facebook and YouTube pages. \\nDetails: http
 s://swatcentral.swarthmore.edu/?trumbaEmbed=view%3Devent%26eventid%3D13420
 77061
LOCATION:Lang Music Building Room 214-Presser Room\, Lang Music Concert Hal
 l\, Lang Music Building Upper Lobby\, Lang Music Building Lower Lobby
URL:https://swatcentral.swarthmore.edu/?trumbaEmbed=view%3Devent%26eventid%
 3D1342077061
CATEGORIES:Performance
END:VEVENT
