SUMMARY:Triumphs and Trials: Women and Queer Comics in Lebanon and the Arab
  World
DESCRIPTION:Organized by: ['French']\\nCategory: Lecture/Panel Discussion\\
 nTriumphs and Trials: Women and Queer Comics in Lebanon and the Arab World
 A public lecture with Tracy Chahwan Tracy Chahwan will discuss the evolvi
 ng landscape of women and LGBTQ+ comics in Lebanon and the Arab world\, fo
 cusing on how marginalized creators develop visual strategies to negotiate
  identity\, censorship\, and socio-political instability. Through autobiog
 raphical practice and case studies\, including her own work in Samandal
  Comics\, Restless by Joseph Kai\, Dans le Taxi by Barrack Rima\, and
  digital platforms like Beirut By Dykes\, this presentation explores comic
 s as a hybrid feminist and queer archive that documents lived experience i
 n contexts where official narratives erase or criminalize it. Tracy Chahw
 an’s work first appeared on the walls of Beirut as street art and poster
 s for local independent music venues. Later\, she began working with the L
 ebanese experimental comics collectives Samandal and Zeez\, eventually pub
 lishing her graphic novel Beirut Bloody Beirut (Marabulles\, 2018). After 
 relocating to the US in 2020\, she turned to journalistic comics contribut
 ing to projects such as "Guantanamo Voices" and "Where to Marie? Stories o
 f Feminism in Lebanon." Her recent work has appeared in The New Yorker\, T
 he New York Times Book Review\, and Middle East Eye. Tracy’s dynamic pra
 ctice reflects her ongoing exploration of the chaotic world around her. T
 uesday\, March 17thLib Lab\, McCabe Library4:15 - 5:30 pm With generous s
 upport of the Arabic Section - Gender and Sexuality Studies - Global Studi
 es - Peace and Conflict Studies - Swarthmore Libraries\\nDetails: https://
 swatcentral.swarthmore.edu/?trumbaEmbed=view%3Devent%26eventid%3D137365328
 0
LOCATION:McCabe LibLab\, Full Space\, Conference Room
URL:https://swatcentral.swarthmore.edu/?trumbaEmbed=view%3Devent%26eventid%
 3D1373653280
CATEGORIES:Lecture/Panel Discussion
END:VEVENT
