SUMMARY:Helen North Memorial Lecture: To Cut Up Nightingales: the Disorient
 ation of Helen Magill\, American Classicist
DESCRIPTION:Organized by: ['Classics']\\nCategory: Lecture/Panel Discussion
 \\nConstanze Guthenke\, Associate Professor of Greek Literature at Oxford 
 University and E.P. Warren Praelector at Corpus Christi College\, will pre
 sent the twenty-third Helen North Memorial Lecture in Classics.  Helen Ma
 gill (1853-1944)\, a member of Swarthmore's first graduating class in 1873
 \, was the first woman to receive a PhD at a U.S. institution\, the co-edu
 cational Boston University in 1877. Her trajectory opens up critical quest
 ions about the imagination of what a professional classicist could be\; ab
 out the triangulated relationship between America\, Europe\, and the ancie
 nt world\; and about the highly ambivalent attitude towards specialist res
 earch.  All are welcome.\\nDetails: https://swatcentral.swarthmore.edu/?t
 rumbaEmbed=view%3Devent%26eventid%3D1325789496
LOCATION:Science Center Room 199-Cunniff Hall Tiered Classroom
URL:https://swatcentral.swarthmore.edu/?trumbaEmbed=view%3Devent%26eventid%
 3D1325789496
CATEGORIES:Lecture/Panel Discussion
END:VEVENT
