SUMMARY:Computers on Film Series: WarGames
DESCRIPTION:Organized by: ['Department of Film and Media Studies'\, 'Comput
 er Science']\\nCategory: Film/Movie\\nA deft and charming thriller blendin
 g Cold War angst with high-school comedy\, WarGames (John Badham\, 1983) 
 tells the story of David Lightman (Matthew Broderick)\, a teenage hacker w
 hose dialup exploits start World War III ... maybe. Professor of Computer 
 Science Keith O'Hara will introduce the film and lead a short discussion a
 fterward. The Computers on Film series is a collaboration between Film & M
 edia Studies and Computer Science\, exploring how computer technology and 
 culture have been represented in cinema over the years. All screenings are
  free and open to the public. Programming made possible by the Kitao Fund 
 for Cinema History Series.\\nDetails: https://swatcentral.swarthmore.edu/?
 trumbaEmbed=view%3Devent%26eventid%3D1374076584
LOCATION:Martin Hall 028 Ping and Rose Chen Screening Room
URL:https://swatcentral.swarthmore.edu/?trumbaEmbed=view%3Devent%26eventid%
 3D1374076584
CATEGORIES:Film/Movie
