SUMMARY:Bartok's Monster: Daedalus Quartet\, Sebastienne Mundheim\, and Pig
  Iron Theatre
DESCRIPTION:Organized by: ['Theater'\, 'Cooper Series']\\nCategory: Perform
 ance\\nPerformances Friday\, March 20\, 8 p.m.  LPAC\, Pearson-Hall Theat
 re    Saturday\, March 21\, 2 p.m. and 8 p.m.  LPAC\, Pearson-Hall Thea
 tre    Inspired by Jay Kirk’s Avoid the Day\, the Daedalus Quartet joi
 ns forces with Pig Iron Theatre Company and visual artist Sebastienne Mund
 heim to present Bartok’s Monster\, a concert and sly lecture-demonstrati
 on about Béla Bartók’s life and work. This kaleidoscopic performance f
 ollows Kirk's research into the Hungarian composer's methods of creation\,
  travels to Transylvania\, and ultimately flirtation with madness. Paper s
 culptures by Mundheim and a movement ensemble including current Swarthmore
  students frame a not-so-academic lecture in this one-hour multidisciplina
 ry performance. \\nDetails: https://swatcentral.swarthmore.edu/?trumbaEmbe
 d=view%3Devent%26eventid%3D1294165004
LOCATION:Lang Performing Arts Center Lobby (LPAC)\, Lang Performing Arts Ce
 nter Room (LPAC)102A Pearson-Hall Theatre
URL:https://swatcentral.swarthmore.edu/?trumbaEmbed=view%3Devent%26eventid%
 3D1294165004
CATEGORIES:Performance
END:VEVENT
