SUMMARY:Sixteen Years - Wrongful Convictions and the Fight for Justice: Fil
 m Screening and Panel Discussion
DESCRIPTION:Organized by: ['Other']\\nCategory: Student Activity (no alcoho
 l)\\nIn January of 1991\, Jeffrey Deskovic\, then 18 years old\, was convi
 cted of the murder and rape of a classmate. His conviction\, based on forc
 ed confessions and false claims despite exculpatory DNA evidence\, led him
  to spend sixteen years of his life in prison. Jeffrey Deskovic is now a p
 owerful attorney and a leader in the field of innocence work\, fighting fo
 r justice in the cases of others who have experienced similar wrongdoings 
 at the hands of a system meant to provide equal protection and justice to 
 all. Join Youth for Innocence Swarthmore for a screening of Sixteen Years\
 , a documentary telling Jeffrey Deskovic’s story of wrongful conviction 
 and his continued fight for justice. After the film\, we will be hosting a
  panel discussion with Jeffrey Deskovic and Jia Rizvi\, the filmmaker of S
 ixteen Years and a powerful voice on wrongful convictions. Her debut docum
 entary\, Conviction\, which explores the shortcomings of the criminal lega
 l system\, screened at 17 festivals worldwide and won six awards\, includi
 ng Best Picture and Best Cinematography. Ms. Rizvi also hosts the true cri
 me podcast Speaking of Crime\, has authored more than 300 articles for For
 bes and has hosted episodes of the Emmy Award-winning show The List.\\nDet
 ails: https://swatcentral.swarthmore.edu/?trumbaEmbed=view%3Devent%26event
 id%3D1364203431
LOCATION:Science Center Room 199-Cunniff Hall Tiered Classroom
URL:https://swatcentral.swarthmore.edu/?trumbaEmbed=view%3Devent%26eventid%
 3D1364203431
CATEGORIES:Student Activity (no alcohol)
END:VEVENT
