SUMMARY:American Martyr: A New Cantata
DESCRIPTION:Organized by: ['Music Department'\, 'Cooper Series'\, 'Music an
 d Dance']\\nCategory: Performance\\nConcert Friday\, March 27\, 8 p.m. Lan
 g Music Building\, Lang Concert Hall   World premiere vocal performance\,
  an original work for soloists\, chorus\, piano\, and organ by composer C.
  Leonard Raybon. Inspired by Murder in a Mill Town by Professor Bruce Dors
 ey\, American Martyr tells the tale of Sarah Maria Cornell – tossed abou
 t by her friends\, family\, and God – searching desperately for love and
  faith in a life cut short. In this new work\, she is made whole\, beatifi
 ed. Featuring vocal performances by students and alums. Presented by Swart
 hmore’s Music and History Departments.\\nDetails: https://swatcentral.sw
 arthmore.edu/?trumbaEmbed=view%3Devent%26eventid%3D1294165006
LOCATION:Lang Music Concert Hall
URL:https://swatcentral.swarthmore.edu/?trumbaEmbed=view%3Devent%26eventid%
