SUMMARY:HEARD External Speaker Series - Jared Clemons
DESCRIPTION:Organized by: ['Lang Center for Civic & Social Responsil']\\nCa
 tegory: Lecture/Panel Discussion\\nThe Healthy\, Equitable\, and Responsiv
 e Democracy (HEARD) Initiative welcomes Prof. Jared Clemons for a conversa
 tion about "the privatization of racial responsibility\," his theoretical 
 framework that provides a new accounting of structural racial inequality a
 nd how it might be addressed politically outside of the education system. 
 Clemons is an Assistant Professor of Political Science at Temple Universit
 y. The event is open to all Swarthmore faculty\, staff\, and students.\\nD
 etails: https://swatcentral.swarthmore.edu/?trumbaEmbed=view%3Devent%26eve
 ntid%3D1368371807
