SUMMARY:On the Air in Changing Times – A German Correspondent in the U.S
DESCRIPTION:Organized by: ['German'\, 'Department of Film and Media Studies
 '\, 'Modern Languages and Literatures']\\nCategory: Lecture/Panel Discussi
 on\\nPlease join us for a talk by Christina Eck\, U.S. Radio Correspondent
  for the German Press Agency DPA in Washington\, DC. Christina has also wo
 rked as a freelance correspondent and producer for German Public Radio ARD
  in Washington\, DC\, as a Reporter\, Anchor\, and Editor for Antenne Baye
 rn Radio in Munich Germany\, and a senior Editor\, Anchor\, and Internatio
 nal Broadcaster for the German Service of Voice of America in Washington\,
  DC.Ms. Eck has been busy covering US-news for German radio for more than 
 30 years and she will take you on a little time travel\, focusing on the c
 ontinuity and change of news and journalism over the decades. This event i
 s sponsored by the German Studies section of the Department of Modern Lang
 uages and Literatures and the Department of Film and Media Studies. \\nDe
 tails: https://swatcentral.swarthmore.edu/?trumbaEmbed=view%3Devent%26even
 tid%3D1370077662
LOCATION:Kohlberg Room 330-Classroom
URL:https://swatcentral.swarthmore.edu/?trumbaEmbed=view%3Devent%26eventid%
 3D1370077662
CATEGORIES:Lecture/Panel Discussion
END:VEVENT
