SUMMARY:Senior Case 2026
DESCRIPTION:Organized by: ['Center for Innovation and Leadership'\, 'Writin
 g Associates Program']\\nCategory: Lecture/Panel Discussion\\nThe Senior S
 howcase provides a space where the Swarthmore community comes together to 
 learn from senior projects across all three divisions. Participating stude
 nts each have three minutes and one slide to present their work. Why only 
 three minutes when our students could spend hours sharing the details of t
 heir projects? Most people will not take more than three minutes to listen
  and understand a student's work\; therefore\, students need to learn both
  how to distill their work into a three-minute sound bite and how to expla
 in their work to a more general audience. Three minutes also allows for mo
 re participation from interested seniors. The Senior Showcase from 3:30pm-
 4:30 Swat Poster Session: 4:30-5:30 (Sci Commons) Refreshments will be ser
 ved after the showcase. \\nDetails: https://swatcentral.swarthmore.edu/?t
 rumbaEmbed=view%3Devent%26eventid%3D1344125710
LOCATION:Science Center Room 101- Chang Hou Hall Tiered Classroom\, Science
  Center Room 101- Chang Hou Hall Lobby
URL:https://swatcentral.swarthmore.edu/?trumbaEmbed=view%3Devent%26eventid%
 3D1344125710
CATEGORIES:Lecture/Panel Discussion
END:VEVENT
