SUMMARY:Spring Dance Concert
DESCRIPTION:Organized by: ['Dance Department'\, 'Lang Performing Arts Cente
 r']\\nCategory: Performance\\nFREE AND OPEN TO THE PUBLIC No Ticket or RSV
 P Required The Swarthmore Dance Department warmly invites you to the Sprin
 g 2025 Dance Concert. The concert will feature a variety of dance styles a
 cross cultural traditions\, including faculty-directed repertory ensembles
  in African\, Ballet\, Contemporary\, Kathak\, Tap\, Taiko\, and a student
 ’s Senior Project by Raquel James ’25. This event is sponsored by the 
 Department of Dance. The closest parking lot to the event venue is the DuP
 ont parking lot on Whittier Pl\, accessible off of Elm Ave. This performan
 ce is taking place in person and will be live-streamed. For those who cann
 ot attend in person\, we hope you join us virtually. Live-stream Link: htt
 ps://video.ibm.com/channel/NC4DHY6VReS Accessibility Advance Notice Swarth
 more College encourages persons with disabilities to participate in its pr
 ograms and activities. If you anticipate needing any type of accommodation
  or have questions about the physical access provided\, please contact the
  event sponsor\, or Susan Smythe\, ADA Program Manager at 610-690-2063 in 
 advance of your participation or visit.\\nDetails: https://swatcentral.swa
 rthmore.edu/?trumbaEmbed=view%3Devent%26eventid%3D1253026796
LOCATION:Lang Performing Arts Center Lobby (LPAC)\, Lang Performing Arts Ce
 nter Room (LPAC) 102 Pearson-Hall Theatre - Full
URL:https://swatcentral.swarthmore.edu/?trumbaEmbed=view%3Devent%26eventid%
 3D1253026796
CATEGORIES:Performance
